owNextMessage?topicID=10991.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#cccccc class=headings><font color=#8b1a1a>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#cccccc class=headings><font color=#8b1a1a>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukixim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kixim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 8:10:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> Hello everyone!<br>I have recently acquired a Tranquil staff - I really like it however it only seems to  proc once a fight (if at all). I am certain this is due to my DEX, and am wondering how much of an effect it would have on the proc rate. My current DEX is 106 (thanks fungi)- any suggestions on good Dex gear that is not too heavy? Off the top of my head I can think of Mushroom Veil and Silken Catfur Girdle. Any other suggestions? Thanks for your help! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upokiri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pokiri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 8:21:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> Cloak of shadows is a bunch... there's always the black pearl jewelry stuff if you're desperate. I haven't personally noticed that dex makes a difference, some days it just seems to proc more than others. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uthwak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thwak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 9:01:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> I agree - I dont know if its worth the effort.  I can only tell a slight difference when I solo or when I have my wifes Shammy buffs on me. <p>Thwak 53 Disciple<BR>Luve 52 Wanderer<BR>Tawk 48 Chanter<BR>of Veeshan<BR>Member of Force of Friends</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uahlianafriar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AhlianaFriar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 9:06:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> You know, I have all kinds of theories about what makes my TStaff proc.<br><br>I have half convinced myself while soloing bats in Sol B that I proc more while fighting a mob in one position than in another. I think this is just a result of the insanity that comes with being stuck in a cave with bats and bugs for hours on end.<br><br>I believe dex does have some overall impact.  I noticed at 255 dex I will proc a lot.  It is actually a lot every fight.<br><br>My dex hovers somewhere around 130ish.<br><br>Sometimes I will get 4 or 5 procs right in a row during a fight.  Those are the fun ones.  Your staff just permastuns the entire fight.<br><br>Other times, I can go an entire fight with none or only one proc.<br><br>Ultimately I think a lot of dex makes a lot of difference, but i wouldn't go changing my gear to proc my staff.  The reward just isn't going to be that great.<br><br>Ahliana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uknuklesninefingers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knukles Ninefingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 482<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 1:35:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> /agree Ahliana<br><br>I notice an increase in the proc rate with HOS cast on me, but the difference is not worth rearranging your gear.<br><br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=147479">Knukles</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulaoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 2186<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 3:06:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1>   I've run tests on this in the past.<br><br>  Bumping my DEX up by ~100 points increases my damage output as a whole due to procs by a whopping 1.7%.<br><br>  Trust me... it's not worth sacrificing AC or HP for. <p><image src=http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/lpb/laokesig2.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uddubois.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ddubois</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 3:43:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> 1.7% sounds so tiny as to be negligable, but...<br><br>By comparison, going from a FBSS to a Sash of Dragonborn while being hasted with Aanya's Quickening is a &quot;whopping&quot; 1.6% (if I had used Celestial Tranquility in the example, it would have been 1.64/1.61 = 1.86%).<br><br>But yeah that I would not make sacrifices to get more DEX, but I wouldn't ignore it either.<br> <p><B>Daniel DuBois</B><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47010">Munnk Twinnk</a> <i>- Level 60 Grandmaster of Tholuxe Paells</i><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3641">Master Mezitt</a> <i>- Level 60 Phantasmist of Tholuxe Paells</i><br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uddubois.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ddubois</A> at: 8/20/02 3:44:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usenseininjin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sensei Ninjin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/02 8:29:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> yeah mushroom veil 12 dex<br>Cloak of shadows 13 dex<br>there is tons of dex items in this game just gotta know where to look. i liek Tstaff but i chose a Kasheks katar/Exquizitevelium battlehammer over it mostly cause the kasheks is a 75 Lifetap <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udistar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Distar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/21/02 10:32:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> You really prefer the Lifetap over the Tstaff stun?<br>Ive got both weapons and sometimes i use the Kasheks if i need a bit more battle spam - but the lifetap never convinced me:<br><br>From my feeling both weaps proc about the same amount if not a bit more procs from the Tstaff.<br>A successful Tstaff proc does 120 dmg and stuns the mob for like 1 or 2 rounds.<br>A successful Kasheks proc does 75dmg and heals 75 while i take 1-2 rounds more mob hits which are well above 75hps usually...<br><br>So for me Tstaff &gt; Kashek's / SOS ...<br><br> <p>----<br>Stibitz - Dwarfen Assassin of Cazic Thule<br>Atramo - Human Disciple of Cazic Thule <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182143">click for Magelo</a><br>Distar - Half Elf Wanderer of Cazic Thule<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulaoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 2198<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/22/02 12:28:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1>   Except, of course, that the stun doesn't work on giant-class / uber mobs, so you only get the DD.<br><br>  The reason most people prefer the lifetap is because it's hugely useful in long AE fights to keep your health up:  I remember when I first got my Gharns I could not believe how much of a difference it made to my survival rate in N ToV.<br><br>  Given the choice between a 120 point DD or a 75 point lifetap, and I'll go for the lifetap thanks.  For the main that's because I don't often fight creatures that a T-Staff is capable of stunning. <p><image src=http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/lpb/laokesig2.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udistar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Distar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/22/02 4:04:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> Thats true Laoke. For a raid situation with long AE fights i can imagine that the lifetap is much better. Less aggro than tstaff and some steady healing.<br>Today my monk is still at a level where i mostly solo or are a groups main tank. In those situations i prefer the Tstaff - but this will surely change as soon as i reach raiding levels...<br><br> <p>----<br>Stibitz - Dwarfen Assassin of Cazic Thule<br>Atramo - Human Disciple of Cazic Thule <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182143">click for Magelo</a><br>Distar - Half Elf Wanderer of Cazic Thule<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulaotzuqigong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LaotzuQigong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 230<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/22/02 6:42:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10991.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff and Dex</span><hr size=1> Tstaff is a very good weapon, but it is somewhat situational when you have a choice of weapons.<br><br>If you're soloing, Tstaff has nice damage output + the stun.<br><br>In groups, it's not always the best choice unless you have alot of caster mobs that are stunnable (like SG).<br><br>On raids, it just draws tons of aggro.<br><br>As for lifetap weapons, many situations they are very nice.  <br><br>XP groups when you're not tanking Lifetap increases mana efficiency tremendously.  I used to do CT with a GIU in offhand and wouldn't need a heal for HOURS.  GIU + fungi is nuts. 8P<br><br>AE mobs/raid mobs, the lifetaps keep you alive a long time and lets the healer concentrate on others.<br><br>If you're ID kiting, hard to beat the lifetap... regen health &gt; stun when the mob is always running heh<br><br>Of course, this is all somewhat dependent on what stats you're giving up for the tstaff... so many 1hb and hth weapons now have great ac + hp that it can easily outweigh the benefits of the tstaff.<br><br>LaotzuQigong<br>60 Grandmaster<br>Legendary<br>The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showNextMessage?topicID=10991.topic">